                },
                "message": "Don't store a PyCFunction in Limited API CyFunction\n\nFixes #7516. (I'm reluctant to fix it just for guarranteed\ndestruction order, because I think that's a bit dangerous to\npromise, but I think the change is an overall improvement anyway).\n\nInstead store the relevant data directly, which should hopefully\nimprove things by giving slightly more direct access.\nI also spotted that the `self` attribute of CyFunctions was never\nchanged and so we can reliably assume its value in most cases.",
